sort_names = ["Bubble", "Selection", "Insertion", "Counting", "Radix", "Heap", "Quick", "Merge"]
type_names = [" ( random [0, 5] )", " ( random [0, 4000] )", " ( almost sorted )", " ( reverse sorted )"]
type_names_title = ["Random [0, 5]", "Random [0, 4000]", "Almost sorted", "Reverse sorted"]
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=8, ncols=2)
fig.set_size_inches(20, 60)
row = 0

for i in range (4):
    if i == 2:
        first = ["Bubble" + type_names[i], "Heap" + type_names[i], "Selection" + type_names[i], "Merge" + type_names[i]];
        second = ["Radix" + type_names[i], "Quick" + type_names[i], "Insertion" + type_names[i], "Counting" + type_names[i]]
    else:
        first = ["Bubble" + type_names[i], "Insertion" + type_names[i], "Selection" + type_names[i], "Merge" + type_names[i]];
        second = ["Radix" + type_names[i], "Quick" + type_names[i], "Heap" + type_names[i], "Counting" + type_names[i]]
    
    data1.plot(x = "Size", y = first, ax=axes[row,0], title=type_names_title[i] + ", array size [50, 300]")
    data1.plot(x = "Size", y = second, ax=axes[row,1], title=type_names_title[i]  + ", array size [50, 300]")
    data2.plot(x = "Size", y = first, ax=axes[row+1,0], title=type_names_title[i] + ", array size [100, 4100]")
    data2.plot(x = "Size", y = second, ax=axes[row+1,1], title=type_names_title[i] + ", array size [100, 4100]")
    row += 2
    
    
for ax_row in axes:
    for ax in ax_row:
        ax.set(xlabel="Size", ylabel="Time (nano)")

plt.show()

sort_names = ["Bubble", "Selection", "Insertion", "Counting", "Radix", "Heap", "Quick", "Merge"]
type_names = [" ( random [0, 5] )", " ( random [0, 4000] )", " ( almost sorted )", " ( reverse sorted )"]
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=8, ncols=2)
fig.set_size_inches(20, 80)
row = 0
for sort_name in sort_names:
    for type_name in type_names:
        data1.plot(x = "Size", y = sort_name+ type_name, ax=axes[row,0], title=sort_name + ", array size [50, 300]")
        data2.plot(x = "Size", y = sort_name+ type_name, ax=axes[row,1], title=sort_name + ", array size [100, 4100]")
    row += 1


for ax_row in axes:
    for ax in ax_row:
        ax.set(xlabel="Size", ylabel="Time (nano)")

plt.show()
